# Web & Admin - Next.js + TypeScript

## Stack
- Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Cloudflare Workers deployment via OpenNext
- Fetch-based API helpers and NextAuth route handlers

## Structure (web-user-app/ and web-admin-portal/)
```
app/                -> App Router pages, layouts, and route handlers
components/         -> Reusable UI and layout components
lib/api/            -> Fetch helpers for `/api/v1`
lib/config/         -> Route and runtime config helpers
types/              -> NextAuth and other shared TypeScript types
auth.ts             -> NextAuth configuration
middleware.ts       -> Locale/auth middleware when present
wrangler.jsonc      -> Cloudflare Workers runtime config
open-next.config.ts -> OpenNext Cloudflare adapter config
```

## Admin Additions
- Sidebar layout with navigation
- Data tables with pagination
- Admin role guard (wraps ProtectedRoute)
- Stats/dashboard cards

## Patterns
- Server Components by default, `"use client"` only when needed
- Auth: NextAuth route handlers with OAuth and/or credentials
- API calls proxy through `/api/v1/[...path]` with `fetch`
- `npm run preview` is the Cloudflare-aware local production check
- Keep secrets in Cloudflare Worker secrets, not `wrangler.jsonc`
- Tailwind for styling and shared design patterns

## Commands
- `npm run dev` or `task web-user-app:dev`
- `npm run build` or `task web-user-app:build`
- `npm run build:cloudflare` for the OpenNext worker bundle
- `npm run preview` for Wrangler/workerd preview
- `npm run deploy` or `task web-user-app:deploy`
- `task web-admin-portal:dev`
- `task web-admin-portal:build`
- `task web-admin-portal:deploy`
